    <scopecontent id="aspace_589e9a525ba15802753dd8bcd14bef99">
      <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
      <p>The collection contains an unpublished autobiographical typescript, "Communism on Campus: Recollections and Comments of a Former Communist Teacher at CCNY," describes Eisenberger's family, youth, education, political views, years at CCNY and his dismissal therefrom, his work at the Gussack Machine Products company, and his later disillusionment with Communism. There is also one small folder of copies of web pages from online exhibitions relating to the Rapp-Coudert firings.</p>
    </scopecontent>
